We've taken skewers to a whole new level with this Jamaican-inspired recipe. Our
jerk seasoning will knock your socks off with a combination of 12 different
herbs and spices. Add in tender chicken, sweet fruit, and curried rice, and
you've got yourself a sweet and savory meal to remember.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees.
If you want to use the grill, fire it up to high. Soak the #wooden skewers{4}
in water. Halve, peel, and finely dice half the @red onion{1} for the curried
rice pilaf. Cut the other half into 1-inch cubes for the skewers. Trim and cut
the @sugar snap peas{4%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, pit, and slice the
@peach{1} into wedges. Cut the @chicken breasts{12%oz} into 1-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #medium pot{} over medium heat. Add the
diced onion and cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until softened. Add the
@basmati rice{1/2%cup} and @curry powder{1/2%tsp}. Toss to combine. Add
1 cup water and the @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil. Cover and
reduce to a simmer for about ~rice{15%minutes}, until rice is tender. During
the last ~{5%minutes} of cooking, stir the snap peas into the rice. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss the chicken in a #medium bowl{} with the @jerk seasoning{1%tbsp}, peaches,
onion cubes, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season generously with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thread the chicken, onion, and peach wedges onto the skewers, alternating
between each. Place onto a foil-lined #baking sheet{}. Broil ~{10-12%minutes},
turning once, until cooked through and lightly charred. You can also cook the
skewers on the #grill{}.

Finish and serve: Cut the @lemon{1} into wedges. Serve the jerk chicken skewers
on a bed of curried rice pilaf. Squeeze over a lemon wedge and enjoy!